quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  8,53,"All this because Allah is not to change a favour He has conferred on a people unless they change their own selves, and that Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing."
  8,54,"(It is) like what did the people of Pharaoh and those before them. They belied the signs of their Lord. So, We destroyed them for their sins and drowned the people of Pharaoh, and they all were unjust."
  8,55,"Surely, the worst of all the living, in the sight of Allah, are those who reject Faith, so they do not believe"
  8,56,"those from whom you have taken a pledge, then they break their pledge each time, and they do not fear Allah."
  8,57,"So, if you find them in war, make them an example (deterrent) for those behind them, so that they take a lesson."
  8,58,"And if you apprehend a breach from a people, then, throw (the treaty) towards them being right forward. Surely, Allah does not like those who breach trust."
  8,59,"And the disbelievers should never think that they have surpassed. Surely, they will not frustrate (the Divine will)."
  8,60,"And make ready against them whatever you can of the power and of the trained horses whereby you frighten the enemy of Allah and your own enemy and others be-sides them whom you do not know. Allah knows them. And whatever thing you spend in the way of Allah, it will be paid to you in full, and you shall not be wronged."
  8,61,"And if they tilt towards peace, you tilt towards it, and place your trust in Allah. Surely, He is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing."